pantheon-monitor (1.1.0-1) testing; urgency=medium

  * added sensors indicator
  * added control of the sensors indicator
  * added checking for the presence of an application in the indicator
  * added choice of processor load view type
  * added sorting sensors
  * added asynchronous sensor update, I think its better
  * Preferences: added a check for the presence of hwmon to display the switch
  * SMART: subtab instead of dialog
  * volume info output changed
  * collect disk read write statistics directly (not libgtop), added nvme support
  * monitor renders fonts correctly in light theme
  * optimized the resource indicator settings
  * replaced custom memory bar with Gtk.ProgressBar
  * abandoned manual drawing of device volumes, use Gtk.ProgressBar
  * updated disk(I/O) monitor view
  * updated cpu activity view
  * fixed: empty drive id (for lvm?)
  * fixed: the layout of sensors popover
  * fixed: network size selection
  * fixed: legend position
  * fixed: maximum percentage of cpu usage

 -- dirli <litandrej85@gmail.com>  Mon, 19 Jun 2023 21:45:02 +0300

